cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.Distributed, cs.AL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a parallel sorting algorithm that minimizes data movement and provides a distributed-memory implementation. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of sampling and histogramming techniques in sorting algorithms. 
3. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper focuses on improving the practical performance of parallel sorting algorithms. 
4. cs.Distributed - The paper provides a distributed-memory implementation of the proposed algorithm. 
5. cs.AL (Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for parallel sorting.
